ments? I might need to check my previous commits and rerun the tests.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Investigating class loading issues**\\\\n\\\\nI’m wondering if the class isn’t found due to JUnit's default package. It seems I should inspect the generated dynamic access reports. It looks like no tests are being run, which could be because the dynamic-access call in the static initializer executes when the native-image builder compiles or initializes LogAdapter at build time instead of during tests. The coverage report may be from the native compilation, which raises questions about how it tracks build-time coverage. I need to explore the tooling for reporting dynamic access.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_2m077th4YGIruWCIqpKQwDx9|fc_0b0864bb725ef9b00169efee4953348193a4923866e791e771\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg \\\"dynamic-access|TrackDynamicAccess|covered\\\" -n buildSrc gradle tests/src/org.springframework/spring-jcl/5.3.15 | head -100\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 14564, \"output\": 331, \"cacheRead\": 4608, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 19503, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777331775948, \"responseId\": \"resp_0b0864bb725ef9b00169efee40ca8c81938221f5850eacce95\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_2m077th4YGIruWCIqpKQwDx9|fc_0b0864bb725ef9b00169efee4953348193a4923866e791e771\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"rg: buildSrc: No such file or directory (os error 2)\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777331785752}]}\n1886:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 0, \"output